.TH "ide_setup_pci_controller" 9 "ide_setup_pci_controller" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ide_setup_pci_controller \- set up IDE PCI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ide_setup_pci_controller
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "int bars "  ","
.BI "const struct ide_port_info *d "  ","
.BI "int noisy "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device
.IP "bars" 12
PCI BARs mask
.IP "d" 12
IDE port info
.IP "noisy" 12
verbose flag

Set up the PCI and controller side of the IDE interface. This brings
up the PCI side of the device, checks that the device is enabled
and enables it if need be
